    "Sanctions" : "Cease and Desist/Injunction"
  } ],
  "Sanction Details" : "From the date of this Order until June 15, 2002, Respondents shall disclose the entry of this Order and the Consent Order to clients and prospective clients by way of the following language in Form U-4 and Parts I and II of Form ADV: \"On December 19, 1997 the Director of the Rhode Island Department of Business Regulation entered a Consent Order (\"1997 Order\") providing that from that date until June 15, 2002, Wealth Management Resources, Inc. (\"WMR\") and Alan S. Wardyga (\"Wardyga\") shall disclose the entry of the 1997 Order and a June 15, 1993 Consent Order (\"1993 Order\") to clients and prospective clients by way of this language in Form U-4 and Parts I and II of Form ADV. The 1997 Order, entered following receipt of written Offers of Settlement from WMR and Wardyga reflecting the express understanding that such Offers were for the purposes of settlement only and that such Offers did not constitute an admission of guilt or wrongdoing, mandates this disclosure and provides that by making this disclosure for the designated five-year period, WMR and Wardyga shall be deemed to have met all present and future disclosure obligations under RI law with respect to disclosure of the 1993 Order and the 1997 Order. The 1997 Order reflects an agreement that, in order to conserve resources and to avoid a protracted dispute of the issue, the failure of WMR and Wardyga to disclose the 1993 Order shall be considered an unintentional, technical violation of RI law. The 1993 Order, entered following receipt of a written Offer of Settlement from Wardyga reflecting the express understanding that such offer was for the purposes of settlement only and that such Offer did not constitute an admission of guilt or wrongdoing, made effective the licensing of Wardyga as an investment adviser and investment adviser representative and o ordered him to cease and desist from any further violation of the licensing requirements of RI law. The 1993 Order ref*See FAQ #1*",
  "Broker Comment" : "THE FOLLOWING DISCLOSURE RELATES TO THE REPORTED OMISSION.  THE MATTER DID NOT INVOLVE A FINDING THAT ANY FALSE STATEMENT WAS MADE OR THAT ANY CONDUCT WAS DISHONEST, UNFAIR OR UNETHICAL.   ON 12/19/1997 THE DIRECTOR OF THE RI DEPT. OF BUSINESS REGULATION ENTERED A CONSENT ORDER PROVIDING FROM THAT DATE UNTIL 6/15/2002 WEALTH MANAGEMENT RESOURCES, INC. AND ALAN S. WARDYGA SHALL DISCLOUSE THE ENTRY OF THE 1997 ORDER AND A 6/15/1993 CONSENT ORDER TO CLIENTS AND PROSPECTIVE CLIENTS BY THE WAY OF LANGUAGE IN FORM U-4 AND PART I AND PART II OF FORM BD. THE 1993 ORDER ENTERED, FOLLOWING A RECEPT OF A WRITTEN OFFER OF SETTLEMENT FROM WARDYGA REFLECTING THE EXPRESS UNDERSTANDING THE OFFER WAS FOR THE PURPOSES OF SETTLEMENT ONLY AND DID NOT CONSTITUTE AN ADMISSION OF WRONGDOING, MADE EFFECTIVE HIS LICENSING AS A REGISTERD INVESTMENT ADVISOR AND INVESTMENT ADVISOR REPRESENTATIVE AND ORDERED HIM TO CEASE AND DESIST FROM FURTHER VIOLATIONS OF THE LICENSING REQUIREMENTS OF THE RHODE ISLAND LAW. THE 1993 ORDER REFLECTS A FINDING BY THE DIRECTOR THAT, WITHOUT EFFECTIVE LICENSING, WARDYGA HAD TRANSACTED BUSINESS AS AN INVESTMENT ADVISOR BY SOLICITING FOR THE SALE OF INVESTMENT ADVISORY SERVICES."
